HEADWORD: Sematic
<hw>Se*mat"ic</hw> <pr>(s⟦esl⟧*m⟦acr⟧t"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>sh^ma</grk>, <grk>sh`matos</grk>, sign, token.]</ety>
<def>Significant; ominous; serving as a warning of danger; -- applied
esp. to the warning colors or forms of certain animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

